The first edition of the “CBI, the 60th year of its existence” conference took place in April and attracted over 200 people from the business and trade community as part of the 21st anniversary celebrations of the Federation of Chambers of Commerce and Industry. This was a milestone event as the Federation celebrated the 21st anniversary of the founding of the Federation in April 2010.
The meeting was organised on 16 April by the Federation’s President, Mr A.D Ravi Shankar. As part of the celebrations, the Federation is organising a series of regional conferences across the country from May, which will conclude with its national annual conference at the end of June 2010 in the northern city of Cochin. The conference, like the recent one in Delhi, will serve to re-assess not only the strategic, technological advances, the best practices and innovative solutions on a global basis, but will also share insights into the challenges facing manufacturing businesses in the current economic environment.
CBI’s Annual Report 2009/09 has a special theme on “The New Manufacturing”. Under this theme we will provide analysis of the current trends and opportunities for manufacturers in the 21st century.
In addition to this, the Federation has provided an interactive website () to the members of the manufacturing industry. This will serve as a tool to communicate and share knowledge between the manufacturers of the Union Territory of Andaman and Nicobar on one hand, and the Federation members and the Indian Industry as a whole.
A total of 50+ national and regional seminars were successfully held to celebrate CEBCI’s 60th year of operations in 2010 in various parts of the country. The Federation is also looking at organizing its first regional conference on a state-to-state basis for all the 22 CEBCI states to commemorate its 60th anniversary next year.
